{"sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"abstract":[{"text":"If there is no value for the given ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"key"},{"text":", returns the description of this key,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"i.e.font family name without the font weight in the end and without whitespaces.","type":"text"}],"kind":"symbol","primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"subscript","kind":"keyword"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"orKey","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"key","kind":"internalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Key","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":") -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"String","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:SS"},{"text":" { ","kind":"text"},{"text":"get","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" }","kind":"text"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"parameters","parameters":[{"name":"key","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The key to use to get a value","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"content":[{"text":"Overview","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"In fact if it seems some rules are missing, or weight are not managed, if the font family only is returned","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the user has an higher probability to use the expected font. Because if a mashup of family name and weight is returned","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"it can produce a PostScript identifier not available, so not usable, so implying a fallback to default system font like ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"San Francisco","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":".","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Because PostScript identifiers in most of cases do not have whitespaces, remove them.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["    \/\/ Given a dictionary with one valu